06/02/2011
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Croatian authorities will request the extradition of a former member of the Scorpions, a Serbian paramilitary unit, from France.
The justice ministry announced the planned request on Saturday (February 5th).
Milorad Momic, 47, suspected of killing Bosniaks in Srebrenica in 1995, was detained in late January near Grenoble.
Croatian Justice Ministry spokesperson Vesna Dovranic said the authorities have collected the necessary documentation for the extradition.
The former Scorpions member was allegedly involved in war crimes in eastern Slavonia.
(Hina, tportal.hr, Danas - 05/02/11)
